<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest <span class="blue">[<span class="yellow">2119</span>]</span> is called '<span class="yellow">Help for Hire</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">60</span> to <span class="yellow">120</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/3438">Lord Vashir</a> [<a href="/area/61">The Towne of New Rigel</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

Greetings Adventurer!  I am pleased to announce I have more job openings<br />
available around the castle, and I want to fill them up fast.  The service<br />
and maintenance around the castle has been slow lately, and since tourism is<br />
one of our biggest money makers, we can now afford more help.  I need people<br />
to clean the castle, guard my valuables, serve my food, and supervise my<br />
workforce.  I need you to visit the various people throughout New R Rigel,<br />
Rune, and Winterbourne Mansion, that I see fit for the task.  I also need<br />
someone to cook my food, so I want you to go visit Lord Agrippas head cook<br />
Kirra, and find out if theres anyone she recommends.  Finally I want a body<br />
guard, someone who I can trust and is trained in many skills of combat.  For<br />
that task you will have to visit Sir Midian to see if there is anyone he can<br />
recommend.  I know you will not fail the task at hand.<br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">40</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">3</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">9,500</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">7,000</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">215</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

Help for Hire consists of:<br />


